,'page','',0),(13,1,'2013-03-01 07:37:01','2013-03-01 07:37:01','[woocommerce_pay]','Finalizar compra → Pagar','','publish','closed','open','','pagar','','','2013-03-01 07:37:01','2013-03-01 07:37:01','',7,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=13',0,'page','',0),(14,1,'2013-03-01 07:37:01','2013-03-01 07:37:01','[woocommerce_thankyou]','Pedido recebido','','publish','closed','open','','pedido-recebido','','','2013-03-01 07:37:01','2013-03-01 07:37:01','',7,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=14',0,'page','',0),(2321,1,'2013-03-11 12:34:21','2013-03-01 22:18:41','<a href=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/bio-space-color-e1362243181298.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/bio-space-color-300x164.jpg\" alt=\"Print\" width=\"300\" height=\"164\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-2372\" /></a>\n\n<p>Biospace é uma empresa de Pesquisa e Inovação em sistemas de Informações para Aeronaves. Desenvolvemos equipamentos aeronáuticos a fim de melhorar e promover a Segurança e a vida de quem os utiliza.</p>\n<div>\n<p>Apresentamos o W-Link 100, a biruta eletrônica. É a evolução da biruta, com um conceito inovador, prático e seguro.</p>\n</div>','A BioSpace','','publish','open','open','','a-biospace','','','2013-03-11 12:34:21','2013-03-01 22:18:41','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=2321',0,'page','',0),(2324,1,'2013-03-01 19:28:15','2013-03-01 22:28:15','<p><a href=\"http://www.abul.com.br/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-2325\" alt=\"ABUL_logo\" src=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/ABUL_logo-1024x74.png\" width=\"717\" height=\"52\" /></a></p>\n<p>A ASSOCIAÇÃO BRASILEIRA DE ULTRALEVES - \"ABUL\", é a entidade civil máxima, de caráter desportivo, que reúne os praticantes do voo em aeronaves ULTRALEVES em todo território nacional, fundada em 14 de março de 1987 e neste mesmo ano reconhecida e autorizada pela ANAC - Agência Nacional de Aviação Civil.</p>\n<p><em>The Ultralight Brazilian Association is a top civilian entity, with a sporty character, that brings together practitioners of Ultralight aircrafts throughout the country. Was founded in March 14<sup>th</sup> of 1987 and at the same year recognized and authorized by ANAC (Brazilian National Civil Aviation agency).</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.inmet.gov.br/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-2326\" alt=\"inmet-logo\" src=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/inmet-logo-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a></p>\n<p><b>INMET – Instituto Nacional de Meteorologia</b></p>\n<p>A missão do Instituto Nacional de Meteorologia (INMET), órgão do Ministério da Agricultura, Pecuária e Abastecimento, é prover informações meteorológicas à sociedade brasileira e influir construtivamente no processo de tomada de decisão, contribuindo para o desenvolvimento sustentável do País. Esta missão é alcançada por meio de monitoramento, análise e previsão de tempo e de clima, que se fundamentam em pesquisa aplicada, trabalho em parceria e, compartilhamento do conhecimento, com ênfase em resultados práticos e confiáveis.</p>\n<p>O INMET representa o Brasil junto à Organização Meteorológica Mundial (OMM) e, por delegação desta Organização, é responsável pelo tráfego das mensagens coletadas pela rede de observação meteorológica da América do Sul e os demais centros meteorológicos que compõem o Sistema de Vigilância Meteorológica Mundial.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>The Brazilian National Meteorological Institute’s (INMET) mission, an agency of the Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock, is to supply meteorological information for Brazilian Society and directly influx on the processes of decision making, contributing for the country’s sustainable development. This mission is accomplished by monitoring, analyses and forecast of weather and climate.</p>\n<p>INMET represents Brazil at the World Meteorological Organization (WMO) and is responsible for the traffic of collected information through the weather observing net of South America and others meteorological centers comprising the World Meteorological Surveillance System.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.parallax.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2319\" alt=\"ParallaxLogo\" src=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/ParallaxLogo.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"53\" /></a></p>\n<p><b>Parallax Inc. </b></p>\n<p><em>Parallax Inc. is a privately held company located in Rocklin, California. Parallax designs and manufactures microcontroller development tools and small single-board computers. Our current product line consists of BASIC Stamp microcontrollers and development software, SX chips and programmers/debuggers, Propeller chips and tools, project boards, robotics kits, educational tools, and sensors.</p>\n<p>Parallax\'s mission is to provide the electronics industry with products that are technically innovative, unique, and economical. This is achieved by a combination of thoughtful, creative design and quality workmanship. To this end, Parallax employees are expected to operate with impeccable integrity. This means being proactive and accountable for one’s responsibilities, being honest at all times, and being courteous to all. Each individual is empowered to contribute to Parallax’s overall goals, and shares in the company’s success.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n','Parceiros','','publish','open','open','','parceiros','','','2013-03-01 19:28:15','2013-03-01 22:28:15','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=2324',0,'page','',0),(2338,1,'2013-03-01 19:59:59','2013-03-01 22:59:59','<h2>Fundadores</h2>\n\n<h3>Jose Trabulse Ferreira</h3>\n<h4>- Diretor Executivo</h4>\nEngenheiro Mecânico, pós-graduado em Administração de Empresas.\n<div></div>\n&nbsp;\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<h3>Ricardo Amaral</h3>\n<h4>- Diretor Técnico</h4>\nEngenheiro Mecânico, possui grande conhecimento em eletrônica, física e biologia.\n\nGosta de velejar, acampar e se isolar em momentos de introspecção. Tem como hobby seus robôs e aeromodelos.\n\n</div>\n','Quem Somos','','trash','open','open','','quem-somos','','','2013-11-26 13:49:46','2013-11-26 13:49:46','',2321,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=2338',0,'page','',0),(2404,1,'2013-03-05 00:43:31','2013-03-05 03:43:31','[woocommerce_lost_password]','Senha perdida','','publish','closed','open','','recuperar-senha','','','2013-03-05 00:43:31','2013-03-05 03:43:31','',9,'http://www.biospace.cc/minha-conta/recuperar-senha/',0,'page','',0),(2411,1,'2013-03-06 12:16:15','2013-03-06 15:16:15','<h3>Dr. Paul Curto</h3>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/paul.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/paul.jpg\" alt=\"paul\" width=\"154\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2421\" /></a>\n\nConhecido como líder mundial em fontes de energia alternativa;\n\nTrabalhou 8 anos como consultor de empresas de distribuição elétrica e depois 16 anos como cientista e engenheiro na NASA, como Chefe de Tecnologia, revisando todos os projetos de Pesquisa e Desenvolvimento em todos os campos de atuação da NASA;\n\nPossui 20 invenções divulgadas, 5 patentes e 85 trabalhos científicos nos 42 anos de profissão;\n\nEspecialidades: Todas as formas de engenharia e ciência, gestão, economia, finanças, política, questões sociais e negócios.\n\nDesenvolveu a primeira casa totalmente abastecida com energia solar em 1974. No MITRE, uma organização sem fins lucrativos, voltada a interesses públicos, liderou um grupo dos 35 melhores cientistas do mundo onde desenvolveram detalhadamente todos os aspectos de engenharia, ciência, socioeconômicos e político de todas as possíveis formas de energia alternativa para o Departamento de Energia dos Estados Unidos (ERDA/DOE), Fundação Nacional de Ciência dos EUA (NSF), e MITRE em 1975-80. Projetaram a primeira usina elétrica solar em Gibbs & Hill entre 1980-83;\n\n\n<em>Known as world leader in alternative energy until the collapse of the field over the Reagan years;\n\nWorked as a utility consultant for 8 years, and later at NASA for 16 years as a scientist and engineer, as Chief Technologist, reviewing all of NASA\'s R&D in every field of endeavor for the NASA Inventions and Contributions Board and the NASA Administrator;\n\nOwns 20 invention disclosures, 5 patents, 85 scientific and technical peer-reviewed papers, 42 years in the profession, and successfully completed 15 projects on time, on budget, and meeting or exceeding specifications;\n\nListed in \"Who\'s Who in America\" for 2009 through 2014, also as \"Who\'s Who In The World\" in 2010 to 2014.\n\nSpecialties: All forms of engineering and science; management, economics, finance, political and social issues and constraints, business, venture capitalism.\n\nDesigned first all-solar home for Ryland Homes in 1974. At MITRE, led a group of 35 of the best minds in the world (including Dr. Edward Teller, among others) who performed detailed engineering, scientific, socio-economic, and political analyses of all alternative energy choices for ERDA/DOE, NSF, and MITRE in 1975-80, and designed solar power plants at Gibbs & Hill in \'80-\'83.</em>','Conselho','','trash','open','open','','conselho','','','2013-11-26 13:49:46','2013-11-26 13:49:46','',2321,'http://www.biospace.cc/?page_id=2411',0,'page','',0),(2427,1,'2013-03-06 13:46:56','2013-03-06 16:46:56','<a href=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/ParallaxLogo.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2319\" alt=\"ParallaxLogo\" src=\"http://www.biospace.cc/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/ParallaxLogo.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"53\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Parallax\'s mission is to provide the electronics industry with products that are technically innovative, unique, and economical.</strong>\nThis is achieved by a combination of thoughtful, creative design and quality workmanship. To this end, Parallax employees are expected to operate with impeccable integrity. This means being proactive and accountable for one’s responsibilities, being honest at all times, and being courteous to all. Each individual is empowered to contribute to Parallax’s overall goals, and shares in the company’s success.\n\n<strong>Parallax Inc.</strong> is a privately held company located in Rocklin, California. Parallax designs and manufactures microcontroller development tools and small single-board computers. Our current product line consists of BASIC Stamp microcontrollers and development software, SX chips and programmers/debuggers, Propeller chips and tools, project boards, robotics kits, educational tools, and sensors.\n\nParallax\'s mission is to provide the electronics industry with products that are technically innovative, unique, and economical. This is achieved by a combination of thoughtful, creative design and quality workmanship. To this end, Parallax employees are expected to operate with impeccable integrity. This means being proactive and accountable for one’s responsibilities, being honest at all times, and being courteous to all. Each individual is empowered to contribute to Parallax’s overall goals, and shares in the company’s success.\n\n<a title=\"Parallax Inc.\" href=\"http://www.parallax.com\" target=\"_blank\">Visite o Site da Parallax Inc. clicando aqui!</a>','Parallax','','publish','open','open','','parallax','','','2013-03-06 13:46:56','2013-03-06 16:46:56','',0,'http://www.biospace.cc/?page_id=2427',0,'page','',0),(2450,1,'2013-03-06 14:10:55','2013-03-06 17:10:55','Esta é a lista atualizada dos bio-aeródromos, onde encontrarão a biruta inteligente / W-Link.\nCompartilhe conosco as suas sugestões!\nbiospace@biospace.cc\n\n<em>These is the updated list of bio-airports, where you can find the intelligent windsock / W-Link.\nAny suggestion please let us know!\nbiospace@biospace.cc</em>\n\n<iframe width=\"875\" height=\"550\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0